parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle snaps in half
or does not retract into the housing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for recall repairs can leave vehicles with safety defects on the road, putting occupants at risk.
symptoms: Dealers are unable to repair recall issues due to lack of parts

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat track anchor bolt can cause the seat to become unstable, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver's seat track anchor bolt comes out

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorbelts can cause the seat belts to malfunction, leading to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The motorbelts do not lock when applying brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear seat belt retractors can cause the seat belts to malfunction, leading to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The rear seat belt retractors fail to tighten with no warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause the vehicle to surge forward, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates on its own
or increases speed without input from the driver
often at low speeds (around 30 mph) or during brake application

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire delamination and failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side
the tire bounces up and down
the tire shows signs of delamination.
